HEADWORD: Polycystina
<hw>Pol`y*cys*ti"na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Poly-</er>, and <er>Cyst</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
division of Radiolaria including numerous minute marine species. The
skeleton is composed of silica, and is often very elegant in form and
sculpture. Many have been found in the fossil state.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

